Mexico Stocks: Empresas ICA SAB and Alfa SAB Shares Decline

-- B y   J o n a t h a n   J .   L e v i n
-- 
2011-07-04T21:58:22Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-04/mexico-stocks-empresas-ica-sab-and-alfa-sab-shares-decline.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in  Mexico  trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 4 p.m. New York time.  The IPC index climbed 0.1 percent to 36,847.10.  Mexico’s manufacturing index fell to 53.3 in June from 53.7
in May, according to the Mexican Institute of Financial
Executives, or IMEF.  Empresas ICA SAB (ICA* MM), the country’s biggest
construction company, slipped 0.3 percent to 26.84 pesos. Alfa
SAB (ALFAA MM), the world’s largest producer of aluminum engine
heads, declined 0.3 percent to 174.38 pesos.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Jonathan J. Levin in Mexico City at 
 jlevin20@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
David Papadopoulos at 
 papadopoulos@bloomberg.net  